<c74object name='dk.cvcross~' category='' module='dataknot'>
    <digest>Separate control voltage into low and high frequency components
</digest>
    <description>The <o>dk.cvcross~</o> object splits incoming control voltage into a low and a high frequency component. In effect this separates slow movements and fast movements into separate signals, allowing you to use the slow movements as &quot;dc offset&quot; and the fast movements as transient shapes.
</description>
    <discussion>This can be used to process MSP signals or actual CV/triggers/gates from modular hardware. This can be accomplished with any DC-coupled audio interface or with specialist hardware like Expert-Sleepers interfaces<br/><a href="http://expert-sleepers.co.uk">http://expert-sleepers.co.uk</a>
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
